Publication date: December 14, 2025

Paid access to the “Lyrica+++” functionality

1. General provisions
1.1. This document constitutes an official offer (a public offer) made by Igor Andreevich Vasserman, a self-employed individual of the Russian Federation, TIN 550145206811 (hereinafter — the “Provider”), addressed to any individual (hereinafter — the “User”), to enter into a paid services agreement on the terms set out below.

1.2. This document is a public offer under Articles 435 and 437(2) of the Civil Code of the Russian Federation.

1.3. Acceptance of this offer (full and unconditional acceptance of its terms) is the User performing the following actions:
– tapping the “Buy subscription” button (or similar) in the Lyrica mobile app (hereinafter — the “App”); and
– successful completion of payment via the payment provider.

1.4. Acceptance of the offer means the conclusion of an agreement on the terms of this offer. The agreement is deemed concluded from the moment funds are credited to the Provider’s account.

2. Subject of the agreement
2.1. The Provider undertakes to grant the User paid access to the extended functionality of the App — the “Lyrica+++” subscription (hereinafter — the “Subscription”), and the User undertakes to pay for the services in accordance with this offer.

2.2. The services are provided remotely in electronic (digital) form. No physical goods are delivered.

3. Subscription features
3.1. The “Lyrica+++” Subscription includes, in particular, the following features:
– Cloud storage for lyrics: synchronization and storage of lyrics across the User’s devices.
– Cloud storage for quick notes: instant synchronization of notes between devices.
– Internal rhymes: enhanced analysis and highlighting of internal rhymes in lyrics.
– Detailed rhymes: enhanced rhyme analysis taking stresses and consonance into account.

3.2. The current list of features is displayed on the Subscription checkout screen in the App and may be updated by the Provider.

3.3. Trial period
3.3.1. The Provider may grant the User a trial period of access to Subscription features on the terms displayed in the App.
3.3.2. The trial period is generally provided once and may be limited per account, email and/or device in order to prevent abuse and fraud.
3.3.3. The Provider may refuse to grant a trial period or terminate it if there are indications of abuse.

4. Price and payment procedure
4.1. The Subscription price is 199 (one hundred ninety-nine) rubles 00 kopecks per billing period, unless otherwise stated on the payment screen.

4.2. The billing period is 30 (thirty) calendar days from the moment the Subscription is activated or from the previous charge.

4.3. Payment is processed via the YooKassa payment provider (LLC NKO “YooMoney”). The Provider does not receive, process, or store the User’s bank card data.

4.4. By purchasing the Subscription, the User agrees to automatic renewal (recurring payments): at the end of each billing period, the fee for the next period is charged automatically from the linked payment method.

4.5. Charging is performed on the date corresponding to the initial payment date (or on the nearest possible date if charging is not possible for technical reasons).

4.6. In case of an unsuccessful charge (insufficient funds, expired card, etc.), access to Subscription features may be suspended until payment is successfully completed.

5. Access provision
5.1. Access to Subscription features is provided automatically after payment is successfully confirmed by the payment provider and technically activated in the App.

5.2. The service is deemed to start when the User is granted access to Subscription features.

5.3. In case of technical issues, the User may contact support: iva28app@gmail.com.

6. Subscription cancellation and auto-renewal
6.1. The User may cancel Subscription auto-renewal at any time in one of the following ways:
– via the subscription management interface in the User’s YooKassa account; or
– by sending a request to iva28app@gmail.com no later than 24 hours before the next scheduled charge date.

6.2. Upon cancellation of auto-renewal, the User retains access to Subscription features until the end of the current paid period.

6.3. The Subscription may be reactivated at any time via the App.

7. Right to refuse the service
7.1. Under Article 32 of the Law of the Russian Federation “On Protection of Consumer Rights”, the User may refuse performance of the agreement before the service starts (before Subscription activation) with a full refund of the paid amount.

7.2. After Subscription activation (service start), refunds for the current paid period are not provided, since the service is delivered in electronic form and is deemed rendered from the moment access is granted. Exceptions are listed in Section 8 of this offer.

7.3. The User may stop using the Subscription at any time by cancelling auto-renewal in accordance with Section 6. Access to Subscription features remains until the end of the paid period.

8. Refunds
8.1. Refunds are provided in the following cases:
– the service was not provided due to the Provider’s fault (Subscription access was not activated within 24 hours after successful payment);
– double/erroneous charge; or
– refusal of the service before it starts in accordance with Section 7.1.

8.2. Refunds are not provided for a service already rendered (after Subscription activation), as the service is delivered in electronic form and is deemed rendered from the moment access is granted. This condition corresponds to Article 25(1) of the Law of the Russian Federation “On Protection of Consumer Rights”, under which the right to return goods of proper quality does not apply to works and services, as well as custom-made goods.

8.3. To request a refund, the User sends an email to iva28app@gmail.com indicating:
– payment date and amount;
– payment identifier (if available);
– the account email in the App; and
– a description of the situation and the grounds for the refund.

8.4. The Provider reviews the request within 10 (ten) business days from receipt. If the grounds are confirmed, the refund is issued via the same payment method used, within the timeframes set by the payment provider and the User’s bank (typically 3 to 30 business days).

8.5. A refund is not provided if Subscription access was activated and the service was being provided, except for the cases listed in Section 8.1.

9. Rights and obligations of the parties
9.1. The Provider undertakes to:
– provide access to Subscription features upon confirmed payment;
– maintain the App’s operability within reasonable limits; and
– generate and provide receipts in accordance with the laws of the Russian Federation.

9.2. The User undertakes to:
– provide accurate information during registration and payment;
– not use the App for unlawful purposes; and
– not take actions that disrupt the App’s operation.

10. Limitation of liability
10.1. The App and the Subscription are provided “as is”. The Provider makes reasonable efforts to ensure stable operation but does not guarantee uninterrupted operation due to circumstances beyond the Provider’s control.

10.2. The Provider is not liable for:
– failures of internet providers, payment systems, or app stores;
– the User’s device malfunctions; or
– actions of third parties.

10.3. The Provider’s total liability under the agreement is limited to the amount actually paid by the User for the last billing period.

11. Personal data
11.1. By purchasing the Subscription, the User confirms that they have read and agree with the Privacy Policy.

11.2. The User consents to the processing of personal data in accordance with Federal Law No. 152‑FZ “On Personal Data” for the purpose of performing this agreement.

12. Governing law and dispute resolution
12.1. This agreement is governed by the laws of the Russian Federation, including the Civil Code and the Law of the Russian Federation No. 2300‑1 “On Protection of Consumer Rights”.

12.2. Disputes are resolved through negotiations. If no agreement is reached, the dispute is referred to the court at the Provider’s location or, at the User’s choice, at the User’s place of residence.

13. Provider status and receipts
13.1. The Provider applies the special tax regime “Tax on Professional Income” (self‑employed) under Federal Law No. 422‑FZ of November 27, 2018.

13.2. For each payment, the Provider generates a receipt and provides it to the User in electronic form (by email or via YooKassa).

14. Final provisions
14.1. The Provider may amend the terms of this offer. Amendments take effect from the moment the new version is published, unless otherwise stated.

14.2. Continued use of the Subscription after publication of amendments constitutes the User’s acceptance of the new version.

14.3. This offer is valid indefinitely until withdrawn by the Provider.

